President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to the President's Management Advisory Board. The Board was established in 2010 to provide advice on implementing best business practices in the federal government. The appointees include Greg Brown, president and CEO of Motorola Solutions, Sam Gilliland, chairman and CEO of Sabre Holdings, Jeffrey B. Kindler, former chairman and CEO of Pfizer, Debra L. Lee, chairman and CEO of BET Networks, Gail J. McGovern, president and CEO of the American Red Cross, Shantanu Narayen, president and CEO of Adobe Systems, Enrique Salem, president and CEO of Symantec Corp, Elizabeth A. Smith, CEO of OSI Restaurant Partners, Tim Solso, chairman and CEO of Cummins Inc, and Ronald A. Williams, chairman of Aetna Inc. The Board will advise both the President and the President's Management Council on matters related to federal government management and operation.